SECTION 1. Tennessee Code Annotated, Title 2, Chapter 3, Part 1, is amended by
adding the following as a new section:
(a) Each county election commission shall collaborate with the sheriff of the
county to establish one (1) or more satellite voting locations in the jail and detention
facilities within the county where eligible voters are confined or detained.
(b) The county election commission shall conduct voting at a satellite voting
location pursuant to subsection (a) on one (1) or more days, for an amount of time to be
determined by the sheriff's office and the county election commission, within the period
for early voting or on election day as determined by the sheriff's office and county
election commission.
(c) The schedules for conducting voting do not need to be uniform among the
satellite voting locations.
(d) If access to the county jail or detention facility is unavailable due to a
lockdown or other exigent circumstances on the date for which in-person voting for
eligible incarcerated or confined individuals is scheduled, then the sheriff's office shall
work with the county election commission to schedule a different date for in-person
voting to be held in accordance with this section.
(e) Only those individuals who are residents of and registered in the county of
their confinement or detention are eligible to vote in-person at the county jail or detention
facility. A satellite voting location established under this section must allow a voter to
