SECTION 2. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 2-7-112(c), is amended by adding
the following as a new subdivision:
(8) A jail roster or other record maintained by a jail or detention facility; provided,
that such identification contains the name and photograph of the voter.
SECTION 3. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 2-7-112(g), is amended by deleting
the subsection and substituting:
(g) Except as provided for under subdivision (c)(8), an identification card issued
by a county or municipality or entity thereof, including a public library, containing a
photograph is not evidence of identification for purposes of verifying the person's
identification on the application for ballot.
SECTION 4. This act takes effect January 1, 2026, the public welfare requiring it.
